  "body": "I was expecting `console --verbosity 2` to not print out the header info (especially to stdout). For example:\n\n**got**\n\n```\n$ echo 'eth.getBlock(\"latest\").difficulty' | console --verbosity 2\ninstance: Geth/v0.9.29/linux/go1.4.2\n datadir: /home/carver/.ethereum\ncoinbase: 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000\nat block: 575787 (2015-06-12 01:31)\n modules: admin:1.0 debug:1.0 eth:1.0 miner:1.0 net:1.0 personal:1.0 shh:1.0 txpool:1.0 web3:1.0\n37722391634\n```\n\n**expected**\n\n```\n$ echo 'eth.getBlock(\"latest\").difficulty' | console --verbosity 2\n37722391634\n```\n",
