    "body": "I didn't think that anyone would be using the console this way but it makes sense. You can even execute scripts this way.\n\nThere are several options:\n1. don't output any information\n2. output it over stderr\n3. add a \"cmd\" flag which executes the command, prints the result and then stops\n4. don't change anything since it is already possible to do this:\n\n```\n± |develop ✗| → echo -e '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getBlockByNumber\",\"params\":[\"latest\", false],\"id\":1}' | nc -U /home/bas/.ethereum/geth.ipc | jq '.result.difficulty'\n\"0x98dbba29a\"\n```\n\nPersonally I'm leaning towards option 3 since it is the most explicit and I like the default welcome message. Especially when you connect to a remote geth instances (future plan) it's nice that you get presented with a small message telling you which node you are connected to and what the current status is.\n",
